## . Project Reflection
Project Title:
Password Security and User Behaviour Analysis

My Role in the Team:
In this project, I was responsible for conducting research and managing data collection. I designed the survey questionnaire and created the Google Form to gather responses. I distributed the form across different platforms to collect data from participants. After data collection, I organized the responses in Microsoft Excel, calculated percentages, and created charts and graphs for the Results section. I also contributed to the Literature Review by identifying relevant research sources and summarizing key findings.

Challenges Faced:
One of the main challenges was obtaining sufficient and timely responses, as many participants either ignored the survey or completed it without giving careful consideration. Another challenge was interpreting raw data and converting it into meaningful insights that aligned with the project topic.

How I Solved Them:
To increase responses, I shared the survey through multiple class groups and personally encouraged classmates to participate by explaining the importance of the research. For data analysis, I compared our findings with existing literature on password security, which helped in better understanding patterns and validating results.

What I Learned from Teamwork:
This project helped me understand that research work is highly interdependent, and each member’s contribution directly supports the overall outcome. I also learned the importance of communication, consistency, and responsibility when working in a team. Additionally, I gained practical experience in survey design, data handling, and basic data analysis.

